---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import SectionHeading from '../components/SectionHeading.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="STEM & Projects"
  description="Maren Stokes' journey in coding, mathematics, physics, and machine learning."
>
  <div class="projects-page">
    <SectionHeading
      title="STEM & Projects"
      subtitle="My journey through code, mathematics, and the pursuit of understanding"
    />

    <section class="journey-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Coding & STEM Journey</h2>
      <div class="journey-content">
        <p class="lead">
          I've been coding since <strong>4th grade</strong>, and technology has always been
          part of how I think and solve problems. What started as simple curiosity and
          experimentation has grown into a deeper passion for understanding how we can use
          computation and mathematics to explain and shape the world around us.
        </p>

        <p>
          Over time, that early curiosity grew into a deeper interest in <strong>applied math,
          physics, and machine learning</strong>, especially how abstract ideas explain
          real-world systems. I love the challenge of taking theoretical concepts and finding
          ways to apply them to solve meaningful problems.
        </p>

        <p>
          Through advanced coursework at LASA, two summers at the <strong>UT Austin Computer
          Science Machine Learning Camps</strong>, and countless hours of independent exploration,
          I've developed not just technical skills, but a way of thinking â€” one that values
          precision, creativity, and the connection between theory and practice.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="interests-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Areas I'm Especially Interested In</h2>

      <div class="interests-grid">
        <div class="interest-card">
          <div class="interest-icon">âˆ‘</div>
          <h3>Applied Mathematics</h3>
          <p>
            Using mathematical frameworks to model complex systems, solve optimization problems,
            and find elegant solutions to real-world challenges. I love the way math provides
            a universal language for understanding patterns and structures.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="interest-card">
          <div class="interest-icon">âš›</div>
          <h3>Physics & Understanding the Universe</h3>
          <p>
            Exploring the fundamental laws that govern our reality â€” from classical mechanics
            to the behavior of complex systems. Physics has taught me to think rigorously and
            see the world through a mathematical lens.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="interest-card">
          <div class="interest-icon">ðŸ¤–</div>
          <h3>Machine Learning & Intelligent Systems</h3>
          <p>
            Building systems that can learn, adapt, and make decisions. I'm fascinated by how
            we can use algorithms and data to create intelligence, and how ML can be applied
            to everything from scientific research to solving societal challenges.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="interest-card">
          <div class="interest-icon">ðŸ”¬</div>
          <h3>Connecting Theory to Real-World Impact</h3>
          <p>
            I'm driven by the intersection of theoretical understanding and practical application.
            The most exciting work happens when abstract ideas become tools that make a
            meaningful difference in the world.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="future-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Looking Ahead</h2>
      <div class="future-content">
        <p>
          I'm continuing to build projects, explore deeply, and learn as much as I can â€”
          especially as I prepare for college and beyond. My goal is to work at the
          intersection of mathematics, physics, and computer science, contributing to
          research and technology that pushes the boundaries of what's possible.
        </p>

        <div class="coming-soon">
          <h3>Project Showcase Coming Soon</h3>
          <p>
            I'm currently working on documenting and showcasing projects that demonstrate
            these interests. Check back soon to see examples of my work in machine learning,
            computational modeling, and algorithmic problem-solving.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .projects-page {
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .journey-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3xl);
  }

  .journey-content {
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .journey-content p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
  }

  .journey-content .lead {
    font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
  }

  .journey-content strong {
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .interests-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3xl);
  }

  .interests-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .interest-card {
    background-color: var(--color-white);
    padding: var(--spacing-xl);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
    border: 1px solid rgba(74, 74, 74, 0.08);
    transition: all var(--transition-base);
  }

  .interest-card:hover {
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .interest-icon {
    font-size: var(--font-size-4xl);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .interest-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .interest-card p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .future-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3xl);
  }

  .future-content {
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .future-content > p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .coming-soon {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary) 0%, var(--color-secondary) 100%);
    padding: var(--spacing-2xl);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .coming-soon h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .coming-soon p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .journey-content .lead,
    .future-content > p {
      font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    }

    .journey-content p {
      font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    }

    .interests-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--spacing-lg);
    }

    .interest-card {
      padding: var(--spacing-lg);
    }

    .interest-icon {
      font-size: var(--font-size-3xl);
    }

    .coming-soon {
      padding: var(--spacing-xl);
    }

    .coming-soon h3 {
      font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    }
  }
</style>
